FOODBORNE ILLNESS - GUATEMALA: (SACATEPEQUEZ) FATAL, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
****************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Wed 10 Apr 2013
Source: Prensa Libre [in Spanish, trans. Mod MPP, edited]
http://www.prensalibre.com/sacatepequez/Intoxicacion-masiva-deja-muertos_0_899310092.html


Three persons died apparently from food poisoning in Santo Domingo Xenacoj, Sacatepequez, and another 32 were admitted to medical facilities with vomiting, diarrhea, convulsions, and severe dehydration, leading the departmental health authorities to declare a red alert in this municipality.

The victims were identified as a 12-year-old male who died in Chimaltenango's National Hospital; his 10-year-old sister, who died in the Pedro de Betancourt facility of Antigua Guatemala, Sacatepequez; and a 27-year-old male who died at home having refused to be taken for medical assistance.

A total of 23 persons were admitted to the Xenacoj Health Center with vomiting and diarrhea and another 9 were admitted to the Chimaltenango and Antigua Guatemala hospitals, according to Amado Quelex from the Municipal Fire Department

A source from the Hospital mentioned that apparently the affected persons had eaten vegetable that they had bought in the local market, and that they could have been contaminated with some chemical product such as pesticides.

The father of the children who died said they had eaten mangos that they had gotten in the market, and that their health status had rapidly deteriorated due to dehydration caused by vomiting and diarrhea.

Members of [another family that had affected members] informed [the press] that they had eaten beans and cauliflower wrapped in egg, and a few hours [later] they had the onset of vomiting and diarrhea, which led them to go to the hospital for medical treatment. They mentioned that the 27-year-old refused to go to the hospital for medical treatment in spite of his symptoms and as a result he died.

Facing this emergency, the Sacatepequez authorities have declared a red alert in the municipality. Calixto Reyes, mayor of Xenacoj, said that as a preventive measure the market has been closed. He added that they will investigate what happened in the market and that they do not know how long it will remain closed. This is the 1st time such a situation has occurred and he was sorry about the deaths of the neighbors.

Case investigation
------------------
Francisco Bermudez, Director of the Sacatepequez Health Zone said that they are investigating the poisoning incident that occurred in Xenacoj.

He confirmed that the focus of contamination was the market and the vendors would be asked to maintain higher levels of hygiene.

Governor Teresa de Jesus Cocoyo indicated in addition to the market, the schools have also been closed.

--
